The article discusses the Global Partnership Against the Spread of Weapons and Materials of Mass Destruction, which is a multilateral initiative aimed at reducing the risk of WMD terrorism. The partnership supports the goal of securing vulnerable nuclear material and radioactive sources worldwide. The Global Partnership countries have contributed over $55 million to the International Atomic Energy Agency's Nuclear Security Fund since 2010. The fund was created in 2002 to support the IAEA's activities in preventing, detecting, and responding to nuclear terrorism. The article lists the 24 partners involved in the Global Partnership.